1
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:12,267
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:12,267 --> 00:00:14,333
[NOA]
<i> Nursing isn't just a job.</i>

3
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:15,767
<i> It's science and soul</i>

4
00:00:15,767 --> 00:00:20,600
<i>stitched together inside
one very tired human being.</i>

5
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,200
<i> I should know.</i>

6
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:24,767
<i>My mom gave
her whole life to it.</i>

7
00:00:24,767 --> 00:00:26,500
<i> And somehow...</i>

8
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,167
<i> I followed her here.</i>

9
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:31,267
<i> It's kind of a Filipino thing.</i>

10
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:36,300
<i>You look back far enough,
across oceans, across decades,</i>

11
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:38,433
<i> and you'll find us.</i>

12
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:40,033
<i> At the bedside...</i>

13
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,567
<i> In the chaos...</i>

14
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:45,433
<i> Holding the line
when everything else gives out.</i>

15
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:47,700
<i> Because Filipinos?</i>

16
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:49,700
<i> We don't just care.</i>

17
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:51,533
<i>- We carry.
- [MUSIC BECOMES MELANCHOLIC]</i>

18
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:56,200
<i>We carry our patients,
their families, their stories.</i>

19
00:00:57,367 --> 00:01:02,767
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

20
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:05,667
<i>We carry the ones
we couldn't save...</i>

21
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:09,533
<i>like, if we hold on tight
enough, it might count.</i>

22
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:12,033
<i> - So, yeah.
</i>- [BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:01:12,033 --> 00:01:15,167
<i>Out of all the places
I could've ended up,</i>

24
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:18,600
<i>I said yes to being
in charge of a ward</i>

25
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,067
<i>people don't even like
to say out loud.</i>

26
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:23,633
<i> Ward 5.</i>

27
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:27,767
<i>Where the patients
don't always check out...</i>

28
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:31,533
<i>and most people with
good instincts transfer out.</i>

29
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:36,700
<i>Which probably says something
about the ones who stay.</i>

30
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:40,167
<i> And some of the patients?</i>

31
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,467
They never really leave.

32
00:01:42,467 --> 00:01:46,500
Yeah, I definitely
didn't think that through.

33
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:48,733
If you hadn't worked
at that 99-cent store,

34
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:50,667
I wouldn't have missed
my audition!

35
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:52,667
- Good morning, sir!
- [OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

36
00:01:52,667 --> 00:01:53,700
But, of course!

37
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,333
Hurry up! I don't want
to get run over again!

38
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:58,300
- Oh, watch out!
- [SHRIEKS]

39
00:01:58,300 --> 00:01:59,833
[LAUGHS]

40
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:01,000
I hate you!

41
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,867
You thought
you were going to die again.

42
00:02:02,867 --> 00:02:05,433
- Have a great day!
- [OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

43
00:02:05,433 --> 00:02:06,733
You guessed it.
[WHISPERS] I see dead people.

44
00:02:06,733 --> 00:02:08,333
[WHISPERS]
I see dead people.

45
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:11,733
[SPECTRAL WIND WHOOSHING]

46
00:02:11,733 --> 00:02:13,400
It's nothing tragic.

47
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:16,233
I'm the only one I know
who's had the third eye since...

48
00:02:16,267 --> 00:02:19,200
[SCREAMING]

49
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:20,233
Oops!

50
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:22,867
Let's shove that back
in the Do Not Open file.

51
00:02:22,867 --> 00:02:24,233
Good vibes only.

52
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:26,167
Kidding!

53
00:02:26,167 --> 00:02:27,367
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

54
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:30,400
Say good morning
to the City of Angels.

55
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,700
And say hello to the newest

56
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:34,767
and most motivated
nursing supervisor in LA.

57
00:02:34,767 --> 00:02:37,133
Hey, hey! It's true, isn't it?

58
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:40,500
This ward is haunted, that's why
nobody wants to work here?

59
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:43,167
Ghost?
[CHUCKLES]

60
00:02:43,167 --> 00:02:45,100
What ghost?

61
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,367
Oh, don't judge.

62
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,867
The proper medical term
is therapeutic denial.

63
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:52,300
[GHOSTLY MOANING]

64
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,733
Did you hear that?

65
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:55,867
- No!
- Yes, you did.

66
00:02:55,867 --> 00:02:57,900
[EERIE HOWLING]

67
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:00,333
Oh! That's why.

68
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,900
What do you mean, "why"?

69
00:03:02,667 --> 00:03:05,433
- [WOMAN ON TV]<i> Surgically...
- She's mad Grey's</i> is fake news.

70
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,500
- He's a...
<i> - That's your medical opinion?</i>

71
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,500
She?

72
00:03:12,467 --> 00:03:14,800
Uh... Yes.

73
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:18,400
<i> - Get Meredith now.
</i>- Almost let my secret slip.

74
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,400
Ghosts stick around
for all kinds of reasons.

75
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,500
Unfinished business.

76
00:03:21,533 --> 00:03:23,333
Guilt, love, hate...

77
00:03:23,333 --> 00:03:25,800
The stronger the emotion,
the more they can mess with you.

78
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,533
- [KENDALL] Dumb show!
- [SLIMY SPLAT]

79
00:03:29,633 --> 00:03:31,367
[VOICE TREMBLING]
Where'd that come from?

80
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:35,533
[SCREAMING]

81
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:37,200
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

82
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,567
[GRIM] I quit!

83
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:42,600
As if real hospitals aren't
crawling with exotics.

84
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,400
[TWINKLING SFX]

85
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,833
Kendall, be nice to the newbies.

86
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,400
No!

87
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,600
[ROS] Oh yeah!
[LAUGHS]

88
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,667
Called it. Hm!

89
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:57,367
Well, that's one
way to clock out.

90
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:59,800
[ROS]
There's another quitter!

91
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:11,600
[UPBEAT PERCUSSIVE MUSIC
PLAYING]

92
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:19,567
[ELEVATOR CHIMES, DOORS OPEN]

93
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:21,567
Staffing's at fifty percent.

94
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:24,333
I need it at a hundred
in four weeks.

95
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:25,600
And while you're at it,

96
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:28,667
get the nurses to stop blaming
the turnover on dead people.

97
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:31,433
- We can't bill for ghosts.
- [PHONE RINGING]

98
00:04:34,533 --> 00:04:36,300
You're probably wondering
why this beautiful,

99
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:39,000
happy, sane girl in front of you
who happens to see ghosts

100
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,667
wants to work
on a haunted floor.

101
00:04:40,667 --> 00:04:42,367
Good morning!

102
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:47,533
With such charming staff.

103
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:50,433
[TRUMPET SQUAWKING SFX]

104
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:52,267
[WHEELS ROLLING]

105
00:04:52,267 --> 00:04:55,600
Well, my beautiful,
sometimes happy,

106
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,500
not-so-sane mother
works here too.

107
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,800
And for<i> Pinoy</i> (Filipino) kids,

108
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,667
becoming a nurse
is like the American wet dream.

109
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:04,833
And now that I'm a sup,
we're prostatically orgasmic.

110
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:10,333
[UPBEAT PERCUSSIVE MUSIC
PLAYING, THEN STOPS]

111
00:05:15,367 --> 00:05:17,000
Are you sure you're ready
for this year?

112
00:05:18,667 --> 00:05:21,700
Taking care of people
is a proud family tradition.

113
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:23,800
[PHONE CHIMES]

114
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,333
Excuse me.

115
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:30,033
[EXHALES SOFTLY]

116
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,767
[DOOR OPENS]

117
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:37,967
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

118
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:40,467
The hard part?
Pretending we're not related.

119
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:44,333
Can't be having nepo vibes
messing with my boss energy.

120
00:05:47,433 --> 00:05:51,700
So, is it Filipino time,
or diva time?

121
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:54,333
Some parents gamble,
drink, do drugs,

122
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:56,600
but my mom's vice? Work.

123
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,733
Who are you talking to?

124
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:01,900
Oh, is that the ADHD thing
they're posting about?

125
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:05,067
No one!
And I'm 15 minutes early.

126
00:06:05,067 --> 00:06:07,367
I'm always one hour early,
because "Filipino time"

127
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,400
doesn't exactly come
with perfect attendance.

128
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:13,367
Remember, if anyone asks,
you don't know me.

129
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:16,067
Oh? Who are you fooling?

130
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:18,567
Mom, Reyes is like Gonzalez
if you're Mexican...

131
00:06:18,567 --> 00:06:20,800
- or Smith if you're white.
- Whatever.

132
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,900
Mm.

133
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:24,700
So, how was the first week?

134
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:27,600
Well, I met everyone.
They're great.

135
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,600
But is everyone always so...

136
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:36,467
[UPBEAT ELECTRONIC POP
MUSIC PLAYING]

137
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:44,833
It's so great to meet you!

138
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:46,733
- What was your name again?
- [GASPS]

139
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:48,433
You don't know me?

140
00:06:50,067 --> 00:06:54,567
Well, then you don't deserve
my welcome gift from my sponsor.

141
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:59,100
Where's my scrubs?

142
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:02,000
You don't even
follow me on TikTok.

143
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:06,033
Ah, Camille, the old child star
in the Philippines.

144
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:09,167
Oh, that's why she kept
asking me for spring water.

145
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:10,767
But did you meet...

146
00:07:11,867 --> 00:07:14,667
Are you buffering or
just building suspense?

147
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:16,700
The hunk!

148
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:23,600
[UPBEAT PERCUSSIVE MUSIC
PLAYING]

149
00:07:26,067 --> 00:07:28,100
You had trouble sleeping again,
huh?

150
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:30,433
Why do your eye bags
look like scrotum?

151
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:32,200
Oh! I'm happy.

152
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,500
Leadership book says,
focus on what you can change.

153
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:39,200
And this ward's got a rep.
Bad morale. High turnover.

154
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,867
What bad morale?

155
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:44,500
[CHEWING]

156
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,133
Americans are so spoiled.

157
00:07:49,167 --> 00:07:51,233
In the Philippines?
You so much as sit down,

158
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:52,733
and you're already out of a job.

159
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:56,067
Back in the day, we only used
a guava branch for circumcision,

160
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:59,033
did it on a basketball court,
under the scorching sun.

161
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:00,467
With a machete!

162
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:02,233
Yeah, sure, Mom. A machete.

163
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:05,867
But let's not forget the
elephant in the room.

164
00:08:05,867 --> 00:08:08,933
Your anxiety pills
totally look like this vitamin

165
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,567
- that I took in Ibiza.
- [PANICKED BREATHING]

166
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,500
Except that one came
with a DJ named Ramon

167
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,033
and a restraining order.

168
00:08:18,033 --> 00:08:20,667
Jane gave me one month
to turn this place around.

169
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,233
And I will.

170
00:08:22,233 --> 00:08:23,700
I just gotta figure out
how to get everyone

171
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:26,133
to work like,
you know, normal people.

172
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:29,167
Just try to understand them,
dear.

173
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:32,767
COVID, then monkeypox,
Alpha, Delta, Omicron.

174
00:08:32,767 --> 00:08:33,967
Just like your ex-boyfriends.

175
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:36,533
Different names
but the same mess.

176
00:08:36,533 --> 00:08:38,867
Especially the white one
with herpes.

177
00:08:38,867 --> 00:08:40,900
Ugh, for the last time!

178
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:43,233
It was a pimple!
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

179
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:46,000
My point is,
we need proper staffing

180
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,200
and the vibes can't be dead
around here.

181
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,667
No offense.

182
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:54,767
There are people who really
don't want to leave

183
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,633
even when their time's up.

184
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:02,067
You're right.

185
00:09:02,267 --> 00:09:05,533
They need a day to
let go and let loose.

186
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:09,267
In my sorority, whenever we
were down, we'd throw a party.

187
00:09:09,267 --> 00:09:12,933
Ah, like a super-spreader event?

188
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:15,700
I'm gonna lift
everyone's spirits!

189
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:16,767
[GIGGLES]

190
00:09:16,767 --> 00:09:18,767
You're a genius, mom!

191
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:21,200
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

192
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,867
[DOOR CLOSES]

193
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:29,233
And almost, finally, Mr. Binks
in 501 claims ghosts are, quote,

194
00:09:29,267 --> 00:09:32,133
"making his bedpans fly."

195
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:34,833
Super excited to make
my special announcement.

196
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:37,767
So dumb.

197
00:09:37,767 --> 00:09:40,833
Well, speaking of
legends and liquids,

198
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:44,233
I once did a commercial
with the Fernando Poe Jr.

199
00:09:44,233 --> 00:09:46,667
That was the Gerber
baby commercial!

200
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,333
Wait! You were a Gerber baby?

201
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:50,700
No. She was the belly.

202
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:57,867
It's like diarrhea.
You just want to squeeze it out.

203
00:09:57,867 --> 00:10:01,700
But the leadership books say,
"Listen first."

204
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:05,733
If there's nobody else, I have
a super exciting announcement

205
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:07,133
and you're all gonna love it.

206
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:09,167
- Oh! I love announcements.
- Yeah.

207
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:10,267
Last time we got excited,

208
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:12,067
Channing Tatum pressed
the wrong elevator button.

209
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:14,933
I wouldn't be caught
dead being a patient here.

210
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:19,333
[DISCORDANT GUITAR STRUM]

211
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:21,167
I can't hold it in any longer!

212
00:10:21,167 --> 00:10:23,067
Surprise!

213
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:26,167
Get ready to fiesta!

214
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:29,367
Cinco de Mayo on Filipino time?

215
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:30,833
Sorry.

216
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:32,033
Booked.

217
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:38,200
My 311,327 followers fight over
who gets to invite me.

218
00:10:38,233 --> 00:10:40,000
Cool, cool.

219
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,667
But I know the rest
of you are holding it in.

220
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:44,867
I think you're great.

221
00:10:44,867 --> 00:10:46,733
Look at Atzin. He's Mexican.

222
00:10:46,733 --> 00:10:48,400
And he's not even excited.

223
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,367
Here's the potluck
sign-up sheet.

224
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:53,967
Not everyone is signing up
at once...

225
00:10:53,967 --> 00:10:55,067
Yes.

226
00:10:55,067 --> 00:10:57,167
Can we, like,
go back to work now?

227
00:10:57,167 --> 00:10:58,633
Yeah! Yeah, yeah, yeah.

228
00:10:58,633 --> 00:11:00,667
I'll just leave it in
the break room.

229
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:04,800
[GASPS]

230
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:11,700
[MARACAS RATTLING]

231
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:13,900
A true leader shakes solo.

232
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,867
Even though the rhythm's dead.

233
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:21,100
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING,
THEN FADES]

234
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:26,067
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

235
00:11:26,067 --> 00:11:30,000
I ain't paying you to play
piñata party planner on my dime.

236
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,400
I'm on break.

237
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,233
[SPECTRAL WIND WHOOSHING]

238
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:34,800
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

239
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:43,700
[WATER POURING]

240
00:11:45,267 --> 00:11:47,333
Why are you making that face?

241
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:50,300
This celebration...

242
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:54,433
is the morale boost
that we need to fix retention.

243
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:58,467
Infection control plan first,
parties later.

244
00:11:58,467 --> 00:11:59,800
All set.

245
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:03,133
Updated SOPs, fall prevention,
patient monitoring,

246
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:05,133
and team communication SOPs

247
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:08,900
to quell rumors
about unseen guests.

248
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:10,100
As requested.

249
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:13,733
Doesn't make sense that
they're only on the fifth floor.

250
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:16,133
They stick around for all
kinds of unfinished things.

251
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:20,733
At least that's what I hear.

252
00:12:20,733 --> 00:12:23,033
Okay, ghost whisperer.

253
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,933
And the SOPs look great.

254
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:28,233
Then again, I've known you
long enough to never doubt you.

255
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:29,367
Thanks, boss.

256
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:32,367
- You're on a break, remember?
- [CHUCKLES] Right.

257
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:34,000
Thanks, friend.

258
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,133
[CHUCKLES]

259
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,100
Do you ever think haters
are going to think

260
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:40,067
that I'm getting
preferential treatment?

261
00:12:40,067 --> 00:12:41,233
Oh, please.

262
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:43,233
First Black D.O.N. here.

263
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:45,200
Haters come with
the badge, baby.

264
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,367
[BOTH LAUGH]

265
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:52,967
Ugh. Tastes like death.

266
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,367
How are you holding up?

267
00:12:57,867 --> 00:12:59,767
Uh, I love my job.

268
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:03,433
Sweetheart, I am not
talking about the job.

269
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:04,867
Third year anniversary
coming...

270
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,133
- [PHONE BUZZES]
- Oh, boss.

271
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:08,033
Time's up! Back on the clock!

272
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:12,200
Let's shove that back
in the Do Not Open file.

273
00:13:15,267 --> 00:13:18,000
You really want
to throw this party?

274
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:22,900
Five percent of nurses
in the U.S. are Filipino.

275
00:13:22,933 --> 00:13:24,000
Thirty percent
of the nurses we lost

276
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,967
during the pandemic
were<i> Pinays</i> (Filipinas).

277
00:13:25,967 --> 00:13:28,400
Now we've got a
whole floor full of them.

278
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,933
And if I've learned one thing,

279
00:13:29,933 --> 00:13:31,767
you celebrate
while you still can.

280
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,200
Well...

281
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:37,300
You have to convince
your Pinays

282
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:41,367
to bring the<i> lumpia
</i>because I can't foot that bill.

283
00:13:41,367 --> 00:13:43,333
Then I better get back to work.

284
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:44,533
See you guys.

285
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:51,567
Oh.

286
00:13:51,567 --> 00:13:54,133
Still nasty. Ugh!

287
00:13:57,267 --> 00:13:59,033
[TESS] No one has signed
up yet?

288
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:04,433
Just tell them you're
my daughter and boom!

289
00:14:04,433 --> 00:14:05,800
Instant potluck!

290
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:09,367
The nurses will even fight over
who gets to bring the lumpia.

291
00:14:09,367 --> 00:14:11,300
I have to do this
one on my own, Mom.

292
00:14:12,567 --> 00:14:16,000
The good book says, "people
don't care how much you know

293
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,367
until they feel
how much you care."

294
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:19,600
Go ahead.

295
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,167
Care harder.

296
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:24,000
Maybe even the ghosts
will sign up.

297
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:30,467
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING
OVER PHONE]

298
00:14:32,567 --> 00:14:34,867
[DOOR OPENS]

299
00:14:34,867 --> 00:14:36,033
Camille!

300
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:38,133
I saw your video.

301
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:40,167
Total star quality.

302
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:42,567
And you even got to share
the stage with, um...

303
00:14:42,567 --> 00:14:45,233
Rustom Padilla?

304
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:48,100
[CHUCKLES] Bet you he's
even hunkier now.

305
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:51,233
You know what?

306
00:14:51,233 --> 00:14:54,133
I don't just sing.

307
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:56,267
I transcend.

308
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:58,100
Wow.

309
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:02,300
That's so... celestial of you.

310
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:05,000
Bring that to the party.

311
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,667
So, you are bringing
a karaoke machine.

312
00:15:07,667 --> 00:15:10,467
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:18,200
[GRUNTS]

314
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:20,533
- [CAR TRUNK CLOSES]
- [HUFFS]

315
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,100
Aah!

316
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,100
Good morning.

317
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,333
Poor girl.

318
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:29,500
She doesn't have a Magic Sing.

319
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,433
- Old tech!
- [SIGHS]

320
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,033
This way, you'll know
which pill is which.

321
00:15:36,067 --> 00:15:37,933
Have you ever wondered
how they make some pills

322
00:15:37,933 --> 00:15:39,967
so round like this?

323
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:41,400
So, have you thought about
what you're bringing

324
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,333
to the Cinco de Mayo party?

325
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:46,033
I can't.

326
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:48,333
We always did Cinco de Mayo
right in Appleton.

327
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,500
Blindfold, stick,
hitting things.

328
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:51,467
If I don't do that,

329
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:53,267
my body doesn't know
that it's a holiday.

330
00:15:54,633 --> 00:15:56,533
Your body?

331
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,400
Oh! [CHUCKLES]

332
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:01,633
A piñata!

333
00:16:01,633 --> 00:16:04,133
No! Pin the tail
on the donkey!

334
00:16:04,133 --> 00:16:05,167
[CHUCKLES]

335
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:08,300
[MOUTHING] What...

336
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:17,200
[NOA EXHALES SHARPLY]

337
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:19,967
There is absolutely
nowhere to hide this thing.

338
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:21,700
Try the trash can.

339
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:31,633
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

340
00:16:47,433 --> 00:16:48,600
[HUFFS]

341
00:16:50,767 --> 00:16:57,733
[ALLURING MUSIC PLAYING]

342
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:03,600
- Oh! Holy crap! Are you okay?
- Don't look! Don't look!

343
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,400
I don't want you to
see all the decorations.

344
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:09,000
And why haven't
you signed up yet?

345
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:11,100
Need to check my shift schedule?

346
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,467
Schedule's in my brain.

347
00:17:12,467 --> 00:17:13,600
Rent free.

348
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,233
Here, let me.

349
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,067
Thanks.

350
00:17:22,067 --> 00:17:23,367
You're working during lunch.

351
00:17:23,367 --> 00:17:24,633
So are your abs.

352
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,733
Did I just say that out loud?

353
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:29,500
Two hundred and fifty dollars?

354
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,533
Does this come
with a mariachi band?

355
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:33,333
The clearance rack seduced me.

356
00:17:34,467 --> 00:17:36,067
You're really
going all out for this.

357
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,567
It's for the team.

358
00:17:38,567 --> 00:17:41,600
I just need help finding
more secret stash zones.

359
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:44,033
I know the perfect place.

360
00:17:44,733 --> 00:17:46,133
But you have to trust me.

361
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,533
[CHUCKLES]

362
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,600
So?

363
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,667
How's this for
our little secret?

364
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:57,667
[CLEARS THROAT]

365
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:00,767
Crap.

366
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:05,367
I'm just going to go
get changed.

367
00:18:05,367 --> 00:18:06,700
- Mm-hmm.
- [CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

368
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,367
I wasn't going to smoke!

369
00:18:12,367 --> 00:18:14,333
- I wasn't going to...
- Girl!

370
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:16,567
Please.

371
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:18,100
With those cakes.

372
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:20,600
She's tasting the rainbow.

373
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:23,233
[IN HUSHED VOICE]
Can't taste the rainbow.

374
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:24,733
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

375
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:26,800
Why am I suddenly
craving Skittles?

376
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:28,800
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

377
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:32,400
Two more days!

378
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:33,667
Cinco de Mayo on the 7th.

379
00:18:33,667 --> 00:18:35,867
I will see you there.

380
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:38,700
Hey! Cinco de Mayo on the 7th?

381
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,233
Have you signed up yet?

382
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:42,100
Aloha!

383
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:43,100
Cinco de Mayo on the 7th.

384
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:46,267
Okay, well, I have
more flyers over there.

385
00:18:46,267 --> 00:18:47,300
[CHUCKLES]

386
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:49,633
Even the walls don't care.

387
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:52,533
The ghosts are
ignoring you, too.

388
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:54,367
- Oh, yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

389
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:56,400
Then I'll have to be
unignorable.

390
00:18:56,433 --> 00:18:57,400
[TESS SIGHS]

391
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,700
[TRUMPET BLOWING]

392
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:05,967
Atzin. Atzin.

393
00:19:05,967 --> 00:19:09,767
I bet you he was hired from
the parking lot of Home Depot.

394
00:19:09,767 --> 00:19:12,133
Dude, you're such a racist.

395
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:14,300
Gay bar, West Hollywood...

396
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:16,267
You're on. You're on.

397
00:19:16,267 --> 00:19:19,800
[TRUMPET BLOWING CONTINUES]

398
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:26,767
[UPBEAT DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

399
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:42,567
So, even though Ward Five
is operating

400
00:19:42,567 --> 00:19:44,633
at a deficit
as far as staffing goes,

401
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:45,633
if you look at the Q4 figure...

402
00:19:45,633 --> 00:19:47,300
[PARTY POPPER POPS]

403
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:51,167
[UPBEAT DANCE MUSIC PLAYING
IN DISTANCE]

404
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:53,367
Excuse me, gentlemen.

405
00:19:56,467 --> 00:19:59,733
[UPBEAT DANCE MUSIC
CONTINUES]

406
00:19:59,733 --> 00:20:02,733
Uh, since this is
already tomorrow,

407
00:20:02,767 --> 00:20:04,833
let's see who's
bringing what.

408
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:08,867
I've got George for...
a box of twinks?

409
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,900
- And Atzin...
- She's here, she's here.

410
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:17,233
My office. Now!

411
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:24,833
Sit down.

412
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:33,333
Look, I asked DonDon to hire
the mariachi band,

413
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,500
- Noa.
- and I honestly thought that

414
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,533
it was going to be something
so great for everybody.

415
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:37,733
- Noa.
- And honestly,

416
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:39,700
this is all I've been
waiting for.

417
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:41,233
Noa!

418
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:43,633
Jane, you don't get it.

419
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:46,767
You are on the clock!

420
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:50,900
Sorry, ma'am.

421
00:20:55,933 --> 00:20:59,667
As your friend,
I should have told you no.

422
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:03,333
As your boss, I have to.

423
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,367
The board's already circling.

424
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:08,800
What happened to haters
come with the badge?

425
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:13,833
- They need this.
- Not them, Noa. You.

426
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:18,267
But what you really need
is a day off.

427
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:22,300
I've already spent eight months
waiting for this--

428
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,667
To bereave!

429
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,433
One month.

430
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:29,567
The ward is gone.

431
00:21:29,567 --> 00:21:33,833
And all those nurses you're so
desperately trying to cheer up?

432
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:35,433
They're gone too.

433
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,567
Ugh!

434
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:44,300
[JANE SIGHS]

435
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:52,333
I shouldn't have asked you
to do this.

436
00:21:55,867 --> 00:21:57,367
You're not ready.

437
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:01,867
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

438
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:04,833
Sorry to interrupt.
We've got a code.

439
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:06,833
[MIMICS EXPLOSION]

440
00:22:09,933 --> 00:22:16,933
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

441
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:38,367
[WATER RUNNING]

442
00:22:51,633 --> 00:22:53,433
We're sorry, Noa.

443
00:22:54,133 --> 00:22:56,767
Yeah. Sorry.

444
00:23:01,433 --> 00:23:08,400
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

445
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:10,333
No, you're not.

446
00:23:14,733 --> 00:23:15,967
None of you care.

447
00:23:15,967 --> 00:23:21,567
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

448
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:22,867
You don't care.

449
00:23:24,767 --> 00:23:28,733
Maybe if you did,
people would want to work here.

450
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:31,400
With you.

451
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:33,067
Noa.

452
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:39,833
Why don't you take
the rest of the day off?

453
00:23:39,833 --> 00:23:40,900
I'm fine.

454
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:44,467
That wasn't a request.

455
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:47,033
You're off the clock.

456
00:23:47,033 --> 00:23:53,933
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

457
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:15,433
Do you want to talk about it?

458
00:24:15,433 --> 00:24:17,067
I said I don't want
to talk about it.

459
00:24:17,067 --> 00:24:19,900
That's what happens
when you don't listen.

460
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:22,167
What are you going
to do? Ground me?

461
00:24:22,167 --> 00:24:23,400
You're acting like
a spoiled brat!

462
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:25,900
[NOA SCOFFS] You work too much
to spoil anyone!

463
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,967
Sorry, I'm a single mother.

464
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:31,567
I'm your personal chef,
personal Uber driver,

465
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,900
psychiatrist,
emotional support anim--

466
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:34,967
- [NOA GRUNTS
- [SHOES SQUEAK]

467
00:24:36,633 --> 00:24:37,600
[HUFFS]

468
00:24:39,767 --> 00:24:40,800
Are you done?

469
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:42,500
No!

470
00:24:43,567 --> 00:24:48,667
Okay, just tell me when you're
ready for some motherly advice.

471
00:24:48,667 --> 00:24:51,900
I mean, I've been doing this
for over 30 years.

472
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:53,433
What do I know, right?

473
00:24:58,733 --> 00:24:59,733
[HUFFS]

474
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:07,800
You know I have to
keep this job.

475
00:25:15,833 --> 00:25:17,133
[TESS SIGHS]

476
00:25:20,267 --> 00:25:23,033
Just let it be for a day.

477
00:25:24,267 --> 00:25:26,733
Maybe then you'll see
what's missing.

478
00:25:31,533 --> 00:25:35,200
Hey, it looks like the
storage area won this round.

479
00:25:36,667 --> 00:25:38,800
Do you need some ice?

480
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:42,833
Or would you like
your dignity back?

481
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:43,867
[NOA SCOFFS]

482
00:25:44,833 --> 00:25:47,067
[TESS GIGGLES]

483
00:25:48,067 --> 00:25:49,633
[TESS SIGHS]

484
00:25:49,633 --> 00:25:51,000
Ugh.

485
00:25:52,767 --> 00:25:56,700
I can't even get the ghost
to stop scaring the newbies.

486
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:02,267
[SIGHING DEEPLY]

487
00:26:05,567 --> 00:26:07,267
They're not going
to fire me, right?

488
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:11,767
Again, that's for
another day, dear.

489
00:26:14,267 --> 00:26:17,767
Let's just pray that
you still have work tomorrow.

490
00:26:20,833 --> 00:26:27,800
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

491
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:37,167
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

492
00:26:41,067 --> 00:26:42,600
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

493
00:26:46,933 --> 00:26:48,200
[SIGHS]

494
00:27:09,633 --> 00:27:11,000
[TUMBLER THUDS]

495
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,133
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

496
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:14,633
[SOFT THUD]

497
00:27:16,767 --> 00:27:17,967
[SIGHS]

498
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:23,767
Good morning, friend.

499
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:25,000
[SIGHS]

500
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,833
Sorry, boss.
I already clocked in.

501
00:27:26,833 --> 00:27:30,633
You're fine.
I'm supposed to be off today.

502
00:27:30,633 --> 00:27:32,667
A-Are you firing me?

503
00:27:32,667 --> 00:27:34,633
No, not yet.

504
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:37,633
But a month's probation stands.

505
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:41,067
Even friends have to
follow the rules...

506
00:27:41,067 --> 00:27:42,600
most of the time.

507
00:27:44,667 --> 00:27:45,833
Where is everybody?

508
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:48,867
Come on.

509
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,167
The board might show up later.

510
00:27:54,167 --> 00:27:56,300
Child, they watch everything.

511
00:28:09,967 --> 00:28:16,867
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

512
00:28:24,167 --> 00:28:25,767
I... Um...

513
00:28:25,767 --> 00:28:27,967
No one wanted Cinco de Mayo

514
00:28:27,967 --> 00:28:30,433
because we already had
something special planned

515
00:28:30,433 --> 00:28:32,300
for your mom's
death anniversary.

516
00:28:33,133 --> 00:28:35,767
And to welcome you.

517
00:28:38,867 --> 00:28:43,100
Your mom hated taking pictures,
so that's the best we could do.

518
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:49,367
[CAMILLE] Your mom and I used to
do TikTok dances together.

519
00:28:52,467 --> 00:28:54,200
We were a perfect duo.

520
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,233
Sorry we lied through omission.

521
00:28:57,267 --> 00:29:00,300
We also figured that's why you
wanted to do something today.

522
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:05,033
- I'm sorry.
- Oh?

523
00:29:05,033 --> 00:29:06,367
Huh?

524
00:29:06,367 --> 00:29:07,333
Just...

525
00:29:13,233 --> 00:29:14,333
[TESS] Hi, dear.

526
00:29:14,333 --> 00:29:16,733
[NOA BREATHES DEEPLY]

527
00:29:18,267 --> 00:29:20,267
They know everything, Mom!

528
00:29:21,233 --> 00:29:23,433
[SOBS] They know everything!

529
00:29:23,433 --> 00:29:26,767
- Why wouldn't they? I--
- No! Stop!

530
00:29:26,767 --> 00:29:28,467
<i>Come on, Mommy Tess!
Come on!</i>

531
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:31,000
<i>Guys, we push as much epi
as we can!</i>

532
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,367
- [PHONE BUZZING]
- [EKG FLATLINES]

533
00:29:32,367 --> 00:29:33,867
<i>You're not doing it right! Move!</i>

534
00:29:33,867 --> 00:29:35,033
<i> We're losing her!</i>

535
00:29:35,033 --> 00:29:37,367
- [EKG FLATLINES]
- [PHONE BUZZING]

536
00:29:37,367 --> 00:29:39,100
<i> 1O:46. Calling it.</i>

537
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:40,800
<i> There's nothing we can do.</i>

538
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:45,867
[SOBBING]

539
00:29:47,233 --> 00:29:48,333
[TESS] I'm sorry, dear.

540
00:29:48,333 --> 00:29:51,867
But do I still need to pretend
that I didn't die?

541
00:29:51,867 --> 00:29:55,267
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

542
00:29:55,267 --> 00:29:58,733
Therapeutic denial...
Therapeutic denial...

543
00:29:59,933 --> 00:30:01,133
Therapeutic denial...

544
00:30:03,933 --> 00:30:05,400
Therapeutic denial...

545
00:30:10,033 --> 00:30:15,000
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

546
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,433
[NOA SOBS]

547
00:30:19,533 --> 00:30:21,500
[CRYING]
Please don't leave me, Mommy!

548
00:30:22,467 --> 00:30:23,867
[NOA CHUCKLES RUEFULLY]

549
00:30:23,867 --> 00:30:26,167
I don't have anybody else.

550
00:30:28,300 --> 00:30:31,400
I'll have to leave you
someday.

551
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,533
But not now.

552
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:36,867
You still need me.

553
00:30:36,867 --> 00:30:43,433
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

554
00:30:50,533 --> 00:30:51,967
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

555
00:30:54,533 --> 00:30:56,133
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

556
00:31:00,067 --> 00:31:01,900
Your mom wasn't joking.

557
00:31:02,567 --> 00:31:03,767
Sorry?

558
00:31:03,767 --> 00:31:05,500
She used to joke that
you can see ghosts.

559
00:31:05,500 --> 00:31:07,567
Can you really see ghosts?

560
00:31:10,933 --> 00:31:12,000
Is she...

561
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:13,200
Is she here right now?

562
00:31:16,900 --> 00:31:18,467
[WHIMPERS IN FEAR]

563
00:31:18,467 --> 00:31:20,600
She said if I keep
being an asshole,

564
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:23,300
she's going to tickle my feet
when I'm asleep!

565
00:31:23,300 --> 00:31:27,533
[TESS] Oh, even the Grim Reaper
is afraid of her three toes.

566
00:31:28,267 --> 00:31:29,233
Tess?

567
00:31:31,967 --> 00:31:34,167
Tess, don't haunt me!

568
00:31:34,967 --> 00:31:37,867
I swear, I'm going
to be a good girl now.

569
00:31:38,867 --> 00:31:40,033
She promises she won't.

570
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:41,967
Really?

571
00:31:43,167 --> 00:31:44,300
[SIGHS IN RELIEF]

572
00:31:44,300 --> 00:31:46,067
[INHALES DEEPLY] Okay.

573
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:50,933
Oh, by the way, can you...

574
00:31:53,100 --> 00:31:56,233
tell your mom that she still
owes me 20 bucks?

575
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,067
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

576
00:32:01,067 --> 00:32:02,033
[KNOCKS ON GLASS]

577
00:32:03,167 --> 00:32:04,267
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

578
00:32:05,133 --> 00:32:06,900
Everything good here?

579
00:32:06,900 --> 00:32:08,100
Just a couple of minutes.

580
00:32:12,267 --> 00:32:14,467
[WHISPERING]
Twenty. Twenty!

581
00:32:14,467 --> 00:32:16,033
[MOUTHING]
<i> Okay, I'll tell her.</i>

582
00:32:19,133 --> 00:32:22,267
- [TESS] Go on, dear. Join them.
- [DOOR CREAKS CLOSE]

583
00:32:22,267 --> 00:32:24,033
They need you there.

584
00:32:24,033 --> 00:32:31,033
["THE DENIAL SONG"
BY JADE RICCIO PLAYING]

585
00:32:37,033 --> 00:32:40,933
[TESS]<i> And don't forget
</i> you need them too.

586
00:32:45,133 --> 00:32:46,433
<i> They will feed you...</i>

587
00:32:53,300 --> 00:32:54,533
<i> take care of you...</i>

588
00:32:57,133 --> 00:33:00,233
<i>and love you as if
you were their own blood.</i>

589
00:33:03,300 --> 00:33:06,233
<i>They might look grumpy
from time to time.</i>

590
00:33:06,233 --> 00:33:08,400
<i> Sometimes, they seem crazy.</i>

591
00:33:11,500 --> 00:33:14,467
<i> But they rely on you.</i>

592
00:33:14,467 --> 00:33:17,133
<i>Even if they don't want
to admit it.</i>

593
00:33:17,133 --> 00:33:24,033
["THE DENIAL SONG" CONTINUES]

594
00:33:27,100 --> 00:33:28,367
[NOA] You're still here, Mom.

595
00:33:30,633 --> 00:33:32,100
<i> We got this.</i>

596
00:33:38,733 --> 00:33:41,167
[MUSIC FADES]

597
00:33:41,167 --> 00:33:42,667
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

598
00:33:42,667 --> 00:33:45,067
[GRIM] The fifth ward's
a hallway, Tess.

599
00:33:45,067 --> 00:33:47,967
Not a home. You're loitering.

600
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:51,733
What do you need now?

601
00:33:51,733 --> 00:33:54,700
You. Heaven's getting impatient.

602
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:59,800
Tell St. Peter I'm not yet due.
I'm still working overtime.

603
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:01,033
Come with me,

604
00:34:01,033 --> 00:34:04,000
or I'll make things
very difficult for her.

605
00:34:04,700 --> 00:34:08,600
I dare you to try.
You'll face my wrath.

606
00:34:11,500 --> 00:34:14,700
[EERIE MORPHING SOUNDS]

607
00:34:14,700 --> 00:34:16,733
Then this is gonna be fun.

608
00:34:16,733 --> 00:34:18,733
[MENACING LAUGHTER]

609
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:33,667
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
